The paper discusses the application of deep learning in embedded systems, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the reduction of necessary resources in deep neural networks, which is a topic in the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper investigates the practical relevance of sparsity in deep neural networks, which is a topic in the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
